headline: Fast-spreading Grand Canyon wildfires force tourist evacuations
description: The White Sage Fire, which is 0% contained, is burning outside the Grand Canyon National Park's North Rim and has scorched roughly 8,700 acres of land. So far, around 500 tourists have been safely evacuated, authorities said on Friday.

description: World number one Jannik Sinner, after a 6-3, 6-3, 6-4 demolition on Centre Court on Friday against Novak Djokovic, will face Carlos Alcaraz on Sunday in the Wimbledon final.

headline: In Srebrenica, 30 years after the genocide, the 'vicious circle' of denial continues
description: On July 11, Bosnia and Herzegovina commemorates the massacre of 8,000 Bosniaks by the forces of Serb General Ratko Mladic. Yet in a country still divided between Muslim Bosniaks, Catholic Croats and Orthodox Serbs, the work of remembrance remains far from unanimous.
